01/09/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The country has made significant positive changes in recent years and the international community is aware of it, Wolfgang Grossruck, vice-president of the OSCE Parliamentary Assembly, said on Thursday (31 August). During a meeting in Tirana, Prime Minister Sali Berisha briefed Grossruck on the latest political developments, including an agreement on electoral reform finally hammered out between the ruling Democratic Party and main opposition Socialist Party. Separately Thursday, President Alfred Moisiu praised the agreement and urged the parties to continue such dialogue. (Albanian News - 01/09/06)
